# Using sod_detect.py from Cursor Terminal

## Setup

Copy `sod_detect.py` to your project's `scripts/` directory.
It is a single-file, zero-dependency Python script (Python 3.10+).

```bash
cp /path/to/sod-skills/scripts/sod_detect.py ./scripts/
```

## Commands

### Check SoD Compliance
```bash
# Basic check — are generator and reviewer from different families?
python scripts/sod_detect.py check \
  --gen-model "claude-sonnet-4-5" \
  --review-model "gemini-2.5-pro"

# With JSON output for audit trail
python scripts/sod_detect.py check \
  --gen-model "cursor-gpt-4o" \
  --review-model "cursor-claude-sonnet" \
  --output sod-compliance.json

# Strict mode — treat UNKNOWN as VIOLATED (for CI/CD gates)
python scripts/sod_detect.py check \
  --gen-model "cursor-gpt-4o" \
  --review-model "cursor-claude-sonnet" \
  --strict
```

### Scan Repository for AI Metadata
```bash
# Scan git log for AI generation markers
python scripts/sod_detect.py scan --repo-path .

# Scan specific files for generation metadata
python scripts/sod_detect.py scan --repo-path ./src
```

### List Known Model Registry
```bash
python scripts/sod_detect.py registry
```

### Validate a Model Pair
```bash
python scripts/sod_detect.py validate \
  --gen-model "gpt-4o" \
  --review-model "claude-sonnet-4-5"
```

