## Pre-Commit Hook
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# .git/hooks/pre-commit
python scripts/sod_detect.py check \
  --gen-model "$CURSOR_GENERATION_MODEL" \
  --review-model "$CURSOR_REVIEW_MODEL" \
  --strict \
  || exit 1
```

## Cursor-Specific Tips

### Determine Your Current Model
The model Cursor is using appears in the model dropdown at the top of
the agent/chat panel. Common mappings:

| Cursor Shows | sod_detect.py --gen-model value |
|---|---|
| Claude Sonnet 4.5 | `claude-sonnet-4-5` |
| Claude Opus 4 | `claude-opus-4-6` |
| GPT-4o | `gpt-4o` |
| Gemini 2.5 Pro | `gemini-2.5-pro` |
| Gemini 3 Pro | `gemini-3-pro` |
| Cursor (built-in) | Check underlying model via settings |

### Background Agent Model Detection
Background Agent output branches include commit metadata. Check:
```bash
git log --format="%B" -1 agent/feature-branch | grep -i "model\|generated"
```
